BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 47.04000000000002 600 Td (Chapter 2: How AI Works \(Simple Explanation\)) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (AI works by looking at thousands of examples and finding patterns.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Imagine teaching a child to recognize cats: you show many cat photos.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Eventually the child knows what a cat looks like. AI does the same.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (There are three basic steps: input, processing, and output.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Input is the information you give the AI, like a question or photo.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Processing is when the AI compares your input to what it has learned.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Output is the answer or action the AI gives back to you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (AI does not actually think or feel - it calculates probabilities.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (It figures out the most likely correct answer based on its training.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Modern AI is trained on billions of text examples from the internet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (This is why it can write, answer questions, and hold conversations.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (You do not need to understand the math - just know it finds patterns.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
