BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 77.75999999999999 600 Td (Chapter 12: AI vs Human Intelligence) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (AI and human brains work very differently despite some similarities.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (AI is faster at math, data analysis, and pattern recognition.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Humans are better at creativity, empathy, common sense, and judgment.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (AI cannot truly understand emotions or have personal experiences.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (A computer can beat a chess champion but cannot comfort a sad friend.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (AI has no consciousness, feelings, or desires of its own.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (It processes information but does not understand meaning the way we do.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (AI cannot learn from a single example like humans often can.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Humans can adapt to completely new situations. AI struggles with this.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (The best results come from humans and AI working together.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (AI handles the tedious parts while humans make the important decisions.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Think of AI as a powerful tool that extends your own abilities.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
