BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 93.12 600 Td (Chapter 19: Glossary of AI Terms) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (AI \(Artificial Intelligence\): Computer programs that can learn and decide.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Algorithm: A set of instructions that tells a computer what to do.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Chatbot: An AI program you can have a text conversation with.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (ChatGPT: A popular AI chatbot made by OpenAI.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Data: Information that AI uses to learn, like text, images, or numbers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Deep Learning: A type of AI that uses layered networks to find patterns.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Machine Learning: AI that improves automatically with more experience.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Natural Language: Regular human language, as opposed to computer code.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Neural Network: An AI system loosely inspired by the human brain.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Prompt: The question or instruction you give to an AI tool.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Training: The process of teaching AI using large amounts of data.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Voice Assistant: AI that responds to spoken commands \(Siri, Alexa\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 296 Td (Large Language Model: The type of AI behind ChatGPT and similar tools.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
