BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 85.44 600 Td (Chapter 20: Resources & Next Steps) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Congratulations! You now understand the basics of AI.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Here are your next steps to start using AI confidently:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (1. Create a free ChatGPT account at chat.openai.com) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (2. Try asking ChatGPT one simple question every day for a week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (3. Explore the voice assistant on your phone \(Siri or Google\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (4. Ask a family member to help you set up a smart home device.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (5. Visit your local library - many offer free technology classes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Free resources: YouTube has thousands of beginner AI tutorials.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (AARP offers technology guides specifically for adults over 50.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Your local senior center may offer computer and AI classes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Remember: there is no rush. Learn at your own comfortable pace.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (The most important thing is to stay curious and not be afraid to try.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 296 Td (You have already taken the biggest step by reading this book!) Tj ET

endstream
